            <description><![CDATA[<h2>ChainLink 0.3.511</h2>
<p class="sub">A quieter guest on your Garmin account, and a full-history Rides graph.</p>

<h3>Your Garmin account comes first</h3>
<ul>
  <li>The ride-history import is now deliberately polite: left alone it waits
  while your latest ride uploads and settles, spreads big histories over a few
  days, and paces every request — with honest status lines in Settings so it
  never looks stuck.</li>
  <li>In a hurry? <b>Pressing Sync yourself</b> imports without the daily
  limit — user-initiated is your call.</li>
  <li>Settings &gt; Garmin Connect gains a <b>"Pause history import"</b>
  switch; new rides keep syncing while it's paused.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Rides graph: the whole story</h3>
<ul>
  <li>The Rides page graph now covers your <b>entire history</b> — switch to
  Years for the full picture, tap any bar to jump there. The list keeps its
  fast paged loading.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Fixed</h3>
<ul>
  <li>The Fitness page's three sub-page cards (Power Profile, Courses,
  Performance Management) work again.</li>
  <li>Training plans created mid-week count the whole week honestly and the
  plan page opens on the correct week.</li>
</ul>
]]></description>
