        <item>
            <title>0.3.507</title>
            <pubDate>Mon, 13 Jul 2026 10:21:50 -0700</pubDate>
            <sparkle:version>507</sparkle:version>
            <sparkle:shortVersionString>0.3.507</sparkle:shortVersionString>
            <sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>14.0</sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>
            <description><![CDATA[<h2>ChainLink 0.3.507</h2>
<p class="sub">Half the disk, clearer form numbers, and a stack of fixes.</p>

<h3>Ride file archive: half the size</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Original ride files are now stored <b>compressed</b> — on first launch
  this build quietly converts your existing archive, roughly halving the
  space it takes. Nothing changes in how the app behaves or performs.</li>
  <li>Settings &gt; Data now shows the archive's size and file count, so you
  can see what's on this device.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Form (TSB) finally speaks plainly</h3>
<ul>
  <li>The Training and Fitness pages' metric pills carry a one-word verdict —
  <b>Fresh / Neutral / Building / Overreached / Too Fresh</b> — with honest
  colours: green only for genuine race freshness, amber for the productive
  fatigue of a training block, red only for real overreach. No more "red =
  you trained properly".</li>
  <li>The charts' form shading follows the same bands, day by day — a hard
  block reads amber, and only the depth below −30 turns red.</li>
  <li>The "What this means" readout now uses the same rounded numbers as the
  pills and names both terms ("Fitness (CTL) 28…").</li>
</ul>

<h3>Training plans: honest week accounting</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Plans created mid-week no longer mis-count: the current week, the plan
  page's week picker and the compliance verdict all follow the plan's own
  Monday-anchored weeks. A big week no longer reads "behind plan" because
  most of it happened before you pressed Generate.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Fixed</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Coach Insights cards expand on tap to show their full text (they were
  clamped to two lines).</li>
  <li>Clicking an upcoming event on the Overview goes to the Events page —
  the editor only opens from the right-click "Edit in Events" action.</li>
  <li>The Fitness page's three sub-page cards (Power Profile, Courses,
  Performance Management) work again on the Mac.</li>
</ul>
]]></description>
